    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - INSTALL - SETTING END PLAY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SETTING END PLAY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Setting end play is done in the vertical position.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When setting end play, the rear bearing cover, yoke and output shaft nut will be installed,
                    removed, and installed again.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>After end play is correct, apply a light coat of Loctite 242 or equivalent to both sides of the
                    shims, case and cover before assembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place transmission in the vertical position with the front end down (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h9">Figure 179</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026h9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026h9" filename="../figg13/G13026H9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 179. Place Transmission in Vertical Position and Temporarily Install Yoke and Output
                    Shaft Nut
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Temporarily install the yoke and output shaft nut. Tighten nut to 300 to 350 ft-lbs. (407 to
                475 N&#8226; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h9">Figure 179</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the output shaft and mainshaft six (6) times clockwise and six (6) times
                counterclockwise to seat the bearings and races (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026h9">Figure 179</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the dial indicator on the output shaft end (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026i0">Figure 180</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026i0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026i0" filename="../figg13/G13026I0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 180. Position Dial Indicator on Output Shaft End and Measure End Play</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pry up on the output shaft to measure end play (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026i0">Figure 180</hotlnk>). End play must be set per the following:
            </para>
            <table id="t130262a">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="sqcolumn1" colwidth="1.5in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="sqcolumn2" colwidth="1.5in" colsep="1"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>FS-5205</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.008 - .012</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>FS-6205/6305</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.006 - .010</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>FS-5306/6306</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>.006 - .010</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove shims for less end play and add shims for more end play.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove output shaft nut, yoke and rear bearing cover. Coat the shims.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the shims and rear bearing cover on the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026i1">Figure 181</hotlnk>). Rear bearing cover top is marked for proper positioning.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13026i1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13026i1" filename="../figg13/G13026I1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 181. Position Shims and Rear Bearing Cover on Case, and Install Retaining Nuts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install retaining nuts and tighten to 60 to 70 ft-lbs. (81 to 95 N&#8226; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13026i1">Figure 181</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Make sure the nuts are properly tightened, the output shaft rotates, and the end play is
                        within specification.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
